i- Why not buy a router?		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - Because it's **expensive** . I bought a Mercury mini 5-port		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    gigabit switch for only 39 yuan; a 5-port gigabit router would		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    cost over a hundred yuan.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - Moreover, a router cannot achieve **independent bandwidth for each		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    device** . The network topology below the router is not		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    transparent to the upper-layer gateway; it is generally considered		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    as a single device, sharing the aforementioned 10 Mbps bandwidth.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    In contrast, a switch only forwards packets and exposes each		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    device to the upper-layer gateway, allowing each device to log in		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    independently and enjoy dedicated bandwidth.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - However, if you need to connect non-programmable smart devices (like		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    smart lamps), spending more on a router is the **most convenient**		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    option.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Will it interfere with the school network?		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - The switch may forward VLAN-tagged packets to the school's		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    gateway. However, without special configuration, since packets		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    from the end network port should not carry VLAN tags, the school		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    gateway will generally discard these packets directly, without		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    interfering with any device.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  - It cannot be ruled out that some abnormal network behavior		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    management systems might detect VLAN packets and ban your account.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    You can only try it yourself or consult your school's IT		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    department.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
